<subSubSection id="F440CB477868FA7498297DAADA4F3A71" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="4A8B1A1D2648FA2CBD7F4953DBFA39D6" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="36C819809735D3CD0C3AF97CC96BFFA1" LSID="65602AB4-9D66-5E80-B7AE-F240074C2BDC" authority="Hering, 1931" authorityName="Hering" authorityYear="1931" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Iragoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Iragoides" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Iragoides Hering, 1931</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FE277F554510604A994C479B2ADF814F" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="7F2D59F87CEEC3E5DFC06425F54028AD" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
<taxonomicName id="5E345154E35F4F6F80266FE9C2A1D602" authorityName="Hering" authorityYear="1931" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Iragoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Iragoides" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Iragoides</taxonomicName>
Hering, 1931, in Seitz, Gross-Schmett. Erde 10: 671 (key), 709. Type species (original designation): 
<taxonomicName id="203C45DE013C414B5A817AE8A8EDF79C" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Miresa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Miresa crispa" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crispa">Miresa crispa</taxonomicName>
Swinhoe, 1890. Type locality India: Darjeeling.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="66CE0445C56835D5FD9ECFEC92AB19B6" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="5CCBB9C51737E85FF0CDEEDCDF97A3F3" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="92959A3A40E029285530C817B52BEFCA" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
The members of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="98504F45139FED97B792BBECE7FEF847" authorityName="Hering" authorityYear="1931" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Iragoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Iragoides" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B8091B9C5C2638999DC94170B7EE94D2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Iragoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are of medium to large size, with a ground colour of reddish brown; the obvious silvery patches are always present on the foreleg and the base of the antennae. In the male genitalia, the uncus and gnathos are well developed; the juxta usually has a pair of finger-shaped lateral processes. 
<taxonomicName id="1DE33D5348E09B2F6EC56E358DCE90E9" authorityName="Hering" authorityYear="1931" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Iragoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Iragoides" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="103DC28307BF301D33DE398E7F11275D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Iragoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
contains four known species to date: 
<taxonomicName id="F99433930D4C20820B7A402A0B188413" genus="I." lsidName="I. crispa" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" rank="species" species="crispa">
<emphasis id="E93D55FA6BD7A9E1AF48A312AB01B6CF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">I. crispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Swinhoe, 1890); 
<taxonomicName id="A5AD564DE928D409B930DC400369C7F0" genus="I." lsidName="I. elongata" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis id="3AB66E2129FD357594C3FEF939995537" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">I. elongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hering, 1931; 
<taxonomicName id="1432E312BB2514786304B90815AF3FB5" genus="I." lsidName="I. dudai" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" rank="species" species="dudai">
<emphasis id="7296A6CF41546BF9DAEEA985971DB143" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">I. dudai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Solovyev &amp; Saldaitis, 2021; 
<taxonomicName id="D1859039113BEFAE3C1D08BA06250D8D" genus="I." lsidName="I. nilgirica" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" rank="species" species="nilgirica">
<emphasis id="40BF5E2B761E7B21827436D69BDF431D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">I. nilgirica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Hampson, 1891), three of which occur in China. 
<taxonomicName id="93E48586AE75D8B2920275A9B3B110B1" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Iragoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Iragoides nilgirica" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nilgirica">
<emphasis id="E750A1754BDCDF490535B1E78C384C5D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Iragoides nilgirica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from India (
<bibRefCitation id="3680784229028245EE4F2166855ED974" author="Wu, CS" journalOrPublisher="Acta Entomologica Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" pagination="753 - 760" refId="B23" refString="Wu, CS, Fang, CL, 2008. A review of the genera Phlossa Walker and Iragoides Hering in China (Lepidoptera: Limacodidae). Acta Entomologica Sinica 51 (7): 753 - 760" title="A review of the genera Phlossa Walker and Iragoides Hering in China (Lepidoptera: Limacodidae)." volume="51" year="2008">Wu and Fang 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="118714ABB2E515B9A2DBA8578CEAEA17" author="Solovyev, AV" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" refId="B19" refString="Solovyev, AV, Witt, ThJ, 2009. The Limacodidae of Vietnam. Entomofauna (Supplement No. 16): 33-229." title="The Limacodidae of Vietnam. Entomofauna (Supplement No. 16): 33 - 229." year="2009">Solovyev and Witt 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="75F32556AC72DCFDE005F840008731E7" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4999.2.1" author="Solovyev, AV" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" pagination="101 - 116" refId="B18" refString="Solovyev, AV, Saldaitis, A, 2021. Five new species of Limacodidae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenoidea) from South-East Asia. Zootaxa 4999 (2): 101 - 116, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4999.2.1" title="Five new species of Limacodidae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenoidea) from South-East Asia." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4999.2.1" volume="4999" year="2021">Solovyev and Saldaitis 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="48A17BB2D7CDDAB1FABE86AF5DA2A6EA" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
In addition, 
<bibRefCitation id="218854B23BAA07289B1B8192BB31C015" author="Wu, CS" journalOrPublisher="Acta Entomologica Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" pagination="753 - 760" refId="B23" refString="Wu, CS, Fang, CL, 2008. A review of the genera Phlossa Walker and Iragoides Hering in China (Lepidoptera: Limacodidae). Acta Entomologica Sinica 51 (7): 753 - 760" title="A review of the genera Phlossa Walker and Iragoides Hering in China (Lepidoptera: Limacodidae)." volume="51" year="2008">Wu and Fang (2008)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="8FC636BBA497FB34BCB6E297F6379E1B" author="Solovyev, AV" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" refId="B19" refString="Solovyev, AV, Witt, ThJ, 2009. The Limacodidae of Vietnam. Entomofauna (Supplement No. 16): 33-229." title="The Limacodidae of Vietnam. Entomofauna (Supplement No. 16): 33 - 229." year="2009">Solovyev and Witt (2009)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="7747D3DCE46E830A591B5993F1739A89" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4999.2.1" author="Solovyev, AV" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" pagination="101 - 116" refId="B18" refString="Solovyev, AV, Saldaitis, A, 2021. Five new species of Limacodidae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenoidea) from South-East Asia. Zootaxa 4999 (2): 101 - 116, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4999.2.1" title="Five new species of Limacodidae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenoidea) from South-East Asia." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4999.2.1" volume="4999" year="2021">Solovyev and Saldaitis (2021)</bibRefCitation>
all presented the male adult of 
<taxonomicName id="6C7F28AF9F42C30DA52FB31107141AA1" authorityName="Hering" authorityYear="1931" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Iragoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Iragoides elongata" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis id="A674EC1819F59C7A1EBBCB4363846B25" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Iragoides elongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in their studies after it was described and illustrated with a hand-drawn adult by 
<bibRefCitation id="2E2218AA656C2C2FE5231B0A89C6A964" author="Hering, M" editor="Seitz, A" journalOrPublisher="Alfred Kernen Verlag, Stuttgart" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" pagination="665 - 728" refId="B4" refString="Hering, M, 1931. Limacodidae. In: Seitz, A, Ed., Die Gross-Schmetteringe der Erde, 10. Alfred Kernen Verlag, Stuttgart: 665 - 728" title="Limacodidae." volumeTitle="Die Gross-Schmetteringe der Erde, 10." year="1931">Hering (1931)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="F33FA0214344E2E57563DECC47B8C08E" author="Wu, CS" journalOrPublisher="Acta Entomologica Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" pagination="753 - 760" refId="B23" refString="Wu, CS, Fang, CL, 2008. A review of the genera Phlossa Walker and Iragoides Hering in China (Lepidoptera: Limacodidae). Acta Entomologica Sinica 51 (7): 753 - 760" title="A review of the genera Phlossa Walker and Iragoides Hering in China (Lepidoptera: Limacodidae)." volume="51" year="2008">Wu and Fang (2008)</bibRefCitation>
also listed both the male and female genitalia. However, as the original description of this species was relatively simple and lacked the description of genitalia, we will redescribe this species below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
